    "discriminators": [
     "Rubber friction: sustained contact noise — high sustain_ratio, low crest, continuous flux, no single onset.",
     "Never front-loaded like IMPACT; more continuous and higher-centroid than MOVEMENT.",
     "The rubber squeak: a shoe on a court, a rubbed balloon, a stretched latex squeal. Stick-slip on a high-friction elastic surface, so the centroid runs HIGH (well above rubber's own impact centroid) and harmonicity climbs into near-tonal territory while remaining unstable.",
     "Steadier in pitch and brighter than LEATHER-CREAK's wobbling groan; less gritty and lower-flatness than PLASTIC-FRICTION's scrape.",
     "Not METAL-FRICTION: a metal screech carries long inharmonic ringing partials; a rubber squeak stops dead the instant the contact stops."
    ],
