    "discriminators": [
     "Rubber is the one damped material that BOUNCES. A dropped ball is not a single transient: it is a train of decaying impulses with MONOTONICALLY DECREASING inter-onset spacing (the bouncing-ball accelerando). The current feature set can only see transient_count > 1 plus a moderate onset_rate and mid-range onset_periodicity — a true bounce detector needs the onset-spacing trend, and until that feature exists this subcategory is under-served by DSP.",
     "Each individual hit is dull and low-centroid with a fast decay: rubber has almost no ring, unlike METAL-IMPACT, and thuds lower and softer than a WOOD-IMPACT knock.",
     "Against CLOTH-IMPACT: rubber is louder, lower-centroid and elastic — it rebounds; cloth lands once and is dead.",
     "Against PLASTIC-IMPACT: plastic is much brighter (centroid ~2.6 kHz vs ~0.9 kHz) and hollow-ringing."
    ],
