     "Dragging, flexing, stretching and flapping rubber: a dark, damped movement bed. Lower-centroid than CLOTH-MOVEMENT (rubber is heavier and its damping is even more low-passed) and with none of paper's bright micro-crackle.",
     "If the stretch turns into a squeal, that is RUBBER-FRICTION; if it turns into a bouncing train, that is RUBBER-IMPACT."
