     "Rare: rubber excited into a pitched, sustained note. Requires a stable f0 and real harmonic energy — the one place a rubber recording looks tonal.",
     "Any file with harmonicity this high is by definition not the material's IMPACT, MOVEMENT or FRICTION sibling. Still far less inharmonic-ringing than METAL-TONAL.",
     "A plucked rubber band or a bowed sheet: a stretched elastic membrane genuinely can hold a pitch, so this is the most plausible TONAL of the soft materials. Expect a low, quickly-damped f0 with few partials — nothing like a METAL-TONAL bell's long inharmonic ring.",
     "The boundary against RUBBER-FRICTION is stability: a squeak has a wandering, unstable pitch; TONAL requires a steady f0."
